msgid "GRSciColl content: Overview - Institutions, collections, sub-collections, specimens"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/grscicoll/modules/ROOT/pages/grscicoll-content.adoc:11
msgid "Representing physical objects and collections online isn’t straightforward. One can represent the information at an infinity of scale: a set of specimens with the same taxon, a drawer, a room, a building, etc. This is why the https://ltc.tdwg.org/index.html[^Latimer core standard] defines its main class as an https://ltc.tdwg.org/terms/index.html#ObjectGroup[^objectGroup] and enables hierarchical representations of these groups. Such flexibility accommodates the reality (and heterogeneity) of physical collections."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/grscicoll/modules/ROOT/pages/grscicoll-content.adoc:13
msgid "However, GRSciColl isn’t as flexible as the Latimer Core standard. Representing the information in GRSciColl means working with a more limited model. There are four types of entries available on the GRSciColl website:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: en/grscicoll/modules/ROOT/pages/grscicoll-content.adoc:15
#, no-wrap
msgid "**Institutions**\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
